    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent. | Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>March 20.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>Your suggestion is a very good one, &amp; should there ever be a new Edition I will consider its adoption.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the relationship between this letter and the <ref target="./DCP-LETT-9894.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter from Horatio Piggot, 20 March 1875</ref>.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">In his letter of 20 March 1875, Piggot suggested that <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1571.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Coral reefs</hi></ref> include illustrations of corals (class Anthozoa). There were no further editions in CD’s lifetime.</note>
        </div>        
            
